32 appropriations, loans, and other moneys from the State, any unit of federal,
33 State, or local government, or any other person, firm, or entity to defray the
34 costs of administering and operating the Program.
35 (9) If necessary, determine the eligibility of an employer, employee, or other
36 individual to participate in the Program.
37 (10) Adopt rules it deems necessary or advisable for the implementation of this
38 Part and the administration and operation of the Program.
